-- China Researcher Says Weak Dollar Benefits U.S., Financial News Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-18T23:44:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/china-researcher-says-weak-dollar-benefits-u-s-financial-news-reports.html
A weak dollar could help the Obama
administration with the upcoming U.S. mid-term election, the
Financial News reported, citing the Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences’ Researcher Li Xiangyang.  A weak dollar could also benefit American exports and help
the U.S. to transfer its debts to other countries, the newspaper
reported, citing Li. The Financial News newspaper is published
by the People’s Bank of China.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  